Major publications on these topics include Sung Birds: Music, Nature, and Poetry in the Later Middle Ages 2007 and Guillaume de Machaut: Secretary, Poet, Musician (2011), which received the Phyllis Goodhart Gordan Prize from The Renaissance Society of America.
In 2016 she was elected as a Fellow of the British Academy.
Elizabeth Eva Leach  is a British musicologist and music theorist who specializes in medieval music, especially that of the fourteenth century.
